relationships.description: The system has one primary database (with redundancy managed internally)
The system performs both offsite and onsite backups
The system may contain a separate SAN device for storage flexibility
The system may contain a separate video recorder if it needs to record more than three shows simultaneously

issues.description: The statement merely cites the standard without specifying what functional safety measures or compliance levels are required.
issues.suggested_fix: Expand this requirement to specify which clauses of IEC 61508 apply and what safety integrity level (SIL) the system must achieve.

issues.description: There is no clear acceptance criteria or test procedures defined to verify functional safety compliance.
issues.suggested_fix: Define pass/fail criteria such as required SIL verification tests or certification deliverables.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall operate on a system capable of multi-processing.

issues.description: The wording "operate on a system capable of multi-processing" is unclear – it repeats "system" and does not specify hardware or OS-level multiprocessing.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether this means support for multi–CPU cores, multi–threaded OS, distributed nodes, or hyperthreading.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall service triggers or stimuli in no more than 500 milliseconds.

issues.description: The type of trigger/stimulus and measurement conditions (peak load, idle, network latency) are not defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify what constitutes a trigger/stimulus, under what load profile, and how timing is measured.

issues.description: No test scenario or tool is identified to measure the 500 ms response time.
issues.suggested_fix: Define a testing approach (e.g., synthetic load test harness) and pass/fail criteria.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall have redundant databases for fail over purposes.

issues.description: The domain model currently associates exactly one Database instance with the System, contradicting the need for multiple redundant databases.
issues.suggested_fix: Update the model multiplicity to 2..* for the System–Database association or introduce a DatabaseCluster class to represent redundancy.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: If system supports recording more than three television shows simultaneously, then system shall have separate video recorder.

issues.description: It's not clear how the system determines support for >3 recordings (software limit, hardware limit, user setting).
issues.suggested_fix: Define the metric or configuration parameter that triggers the conditional requirement.

issues.description: REQ-010 and REQ-011 both mention a separate video recorder but use different triggers (optional vs. conditional), causing potential overlap.
issues.suggested_fix: Consolidate into a single requirement that describes optional installation and conditional mandate based on simultaneous recording capacity.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: SH system shall be usable by those with slight eye loss.

issues.description: "Slight eye loss" is subjective and not mapped to any accessibility guideline or visual acuity measurement.
issues.suggested_fix: Reference a standard (e.g., WCAG contrast ratios, minimum font size) or specify quantitative visual acuity requirements.

issues.description: No acceptance criteria or test scenarios are defined to evaluate usability by visually impaired users.
issues.suggested_fix: Define usability tests (e.g., with sample users, task completion time limits) and performance thresholds.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall be easy to use.

issues.description: "Easy to use" is a qualitative statement without measurable criteria.
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific usability metrics, e.g., average time to complete common tasks, error rate below X%, satisfaction survey scores.

issues.description: No testable acceptance criteria are provided for evaluating ease of use.
issues.suggested_fix: Include usability testing plans and success criteria in the requirement.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: System shall not record any new shows if there is space available for recovery.

issues.description: The clause contradicts standard behavior: if space is available, the system should record new shows rather than forbid it.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify intent—perhaps it meant "if no space is available for recovery" or implement a FIFO-based eviction policy.

domain_model_issues.description: The System class lacks attributes and methods to model UI constraints (buttonSize, backlighting, fontSizeOptions), accessibility features, notifications, and user preferences.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add classes and attributes such as UserInterfaceSettings (buttonSize:Dimension, backlightEnabled:Boolean, fontSizeRange:Range), AccessibilityProfile, and NotificationSettings.

domain_model_issues.description: Multiplicity is 1..1 but requirement REQ-006 demands multiple redundant databases.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Change the targetMultiplicity to 2..* or introduce a DatabaseCluster association class capturing primary and standby instances.

domain_model_issues.description: Multiplicity from System to VideoRecorder is optional (0..1), but REQ-011 mandates one when >3 recordings are needed.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a conditional constraint on the association or model a RecordingCapability attribute on System instead of a hard multiplicity.

domain_model_issues.description: Backup has only onsite/offsite flags; lacks schedule, data scope (configuration vs. reporting), retention policy.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like schedule:CronExpression, dataTypes:List<String>, retentionPeriod:Duration.

domain_model_issues.description: The model has no class to represent user notifications, delivery channels, or event subscriptions, yet many requirements refer to notifications.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a Notification class with attributes channel (email/SMS/push), userPrefs, and a relationship from System to Notification.

domain_model_issues.description: No generic Sensor or specialized sensor classes (TemperatureSensor, MotionDetector, WaterFlowSensor, AirQualitySensor) are present despite extensive sensor requirements.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Define a Sensor superclass and subclasses for each type, with attributes reading, threshold, timestamp, unit.

domain_model_issues.description: User preferences, authentication, and profile data are referenced (e.g., thresholds, schedules), but no User or Profile class exists.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a User class with associations to Preference, Profile, and Role classes.

domain_model_issues.description: Redundancy is only handled by a boolean attribute on Database; complex fail-over clustering and health-check relationships are not modeled.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Model a DatabaseCluster class with instances of Database, healthStatus, failoverStrategy, and link System to DatabaseCluster instead of a single Database.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement mandates encryption of communications between the System and remote or internal components.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall encrypt all communications between internal components and any remote interfaces using industry-standard protocols (e.g., TLS 1.2 or higher).
missing_requirements.rationale: The system handles sensitive control and monitoring data (e.g., door‐lock commands, camera feeds, user notifications). Without encryption, data in transit can be intercepted or manipulated.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement specifies user authentication or role‐based access control for local and remote interfaces.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall require user authentication and enforce role‐based access control for all local and remote interfaces, ensuring only authorized users can perform specific actions (e.g., unlocking doors, arming security).
missing_requirements.rationale: The system offers critical operations (remote door unlock, HVAC settings, camera access). Restricting actions to authenticated, authorized users is essential to prevent misuse.

missing_requirements.description: There is no requirement for logging or audit trails of user actions and system events.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall maintain an audit log of all user commands, configuration changes, and system events with timestamps and user identifiers, and shall retain these logs for at least one year.
missing_requirements.rationale: To support troubleshooting, regulatory compliance, and forensic analysis after security or operational incidents, a detailed audit trail is necessary.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement governs how software or firmware updates will be applied to the System or attached devices.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall support secure remote software and firmware updates for itself and attached subsystems, and provide a rollback mechanism to revert to the last known good version in case of update failure.
missing_requirements.rationale: Given the wide range of controlled devices and security implications, the system must be easily and safely maintained without physical intervention.

missing_requirements.description: Requirement REQ-007 specifies periodic backups but omits how administrators configure backup frequency, retention, and encryption.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall provide a configuration interface allowing administrators to define onsite and offsite backup schedules (frequency and time), retention periods, and encryption settings, and enforce these parameters during backup operations.
missing_requirements.rationale: Administrators need control over when and how long backups are kept, and must ensure offsite data is protected.

missing_requirements.description: There is no requirement describing how to restore data from backups.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall allow administrators to manually initiate restore operations from both onsite and offsite backups, selecting specific backup dates and times via the user interface.
missing_requirements.rationale: Without restore functionality, backups cannot be utilized to recover from data loss or configuration errors.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement mandates integrity verification of backups.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall automatically verify the integrity of onsite and offsite backups at least once per month and notify administrators of any verification failures.
missing_requirements.rationale: To ensure that backup data is recoverable when needed, routine verification is essential.

missing_requirements.description: REQ-006 requires redundant databases, but failover detection time and switchover behavior are undefined.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall detect primary database failure within 2 seconds and automatically switch all transactional operations to the redundant database within 1 second of detection.
missing_requirements.rationale: Explicit timing for failover ensures service continuity and meets availability targets.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement specifies the replication mode between primary and redundant databases to avoid data loss.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall replicate transactions synchronously from the primary database to the redundant database to guarantee zero data loss upon failover.
missing_requirements.rationale: Synchronous replication is needed to maintain consistency between databases and prevent transaction loss during a switchover.

missing_requirements.description: Domain model includes optional SANDevice but no requirement defines how to manage attachment or removal.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall allow administrators to dynamically add, configure, and remove SAN devices at runtime without requiring system shutdown, and shall automatically detect and validate any attached SANDevice.
missing_requirements.rationale: To provide storage flexibility without downtime, the system must support live SAN device management.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement covers health and availability monitoring of an attached VideoRecorder device.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall continuously monitor the availability and performance of any attached VideoRecorder and notify administrators within 5 minutes of any device failure or service degradation.
missing_requirements.rationale: Ensuring video recording reliability requires active monitoring of the optional VideoRecorder subsystem.

missing_requirements.description: There is no requirement for encrypting sensitive data at rest in the database or backups.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System shall encrypt all sensitive data at rest in primary and redundant databases, as well as in onsite and offsite backups, using AES-256 or stronger encryption.
missing_requirements.rationale: Protecting stored user data, configuration, and audit logs from unauthorized access requires strong encryption at rest.
